  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "A large watercolor and gouache on parchment (575 x 430 mm) by **Pauline Rifer de Courcelles** (Paris, 1781 – 1851), also known professionally as **Madame Knip**, dated 1811, depicting a male **Red Bird-of-Paradise** (*Paradisaea rubra* Daudin, 1800) perched on a branch. Made at the peak of the artist's career — the same year as her celebrated publication *Les Pigeons* (with Coenraad Jacob Temminck). Purchased at **Christie's Paris, 22 November 2022, lot 1** (hammer price €80,000; total with buyer's premium €100,800), with support from a named foundation (see credit line discrepancy below). Designated one of Teylers' **50 Topstukken**.\n\n**Family connection:** Pauline Rifer de Courcelles was the stepmother of **Henriëtte Ronner-Knip** (1821–1909), the cat painter whose work is also in the Teylers Topstukken collection (KS 135).",
